            "content": "# Claude Code Agent Teams — Implementation Research\n\n> **Research date:** 2026-03-03\n> **Claude Code version analyzed:** v2.1.63 (Bun compiled binary)\n> **Source:** Decompiled from installed binary (CC is NOT open source — GitHub repo is issue tracker only)\n> **Verification:** Re-run decompilation after CC updates to check for interface changes\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [Architecture Overview](#architecture-overview)\n2. [Backend Detection Logic](#backend-detection-logic)\n3. [Backend Interface](#backend-interface)\n4. [tmux Backend — Full Implementation](#tmux-backend)\n5. [iTerm2 Backend — Full Implementation](#iterm2-backend)\n6. [In-Process Backend](#in-process-backend)\n7. [PaneBackendExecutor — Lifecycle Wrapper](#panebackendexecutor)\n8. [Teammate Spawn Flow](#teammate-spawn-flow)\n9. [Communication — Mailbox System](#mailbox-system)\n10. [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)\n11. [Known Bugs](#known-bugs)\n12. [TUIC Integration Strategy](#tuic-integration-strategy)\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nClaude Code Agent Teams has three layers:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Team Lead (orchestrator)               │\n│  - Decides to spawn teammates           │\n│  - Assigns tasks via shared task list   │\n│  - Sends messages via mailbox           │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  PaneBackendExecutor (lifecycle)        │\n│  - Wraps any backend                    │\n│  - Manages spawn/kill/message/terminate │\n│  - Tracks teammates in Map              │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Backend (terminal multiplexer)         │\n│  - tmux | iTerm2 | in-process           │\n│  - Creates panes, sends commands        │\n│  - Visual management (borders, titles)  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nCommunication (file-based, backend-independent):\n  ~/.claude/teams/{teamName}/config.json     — team config\n  ~/.claude/teams/{teamName}/messages/       — mailbox\n  ~/.claude/tasks/{teamName}/                — shared task list\n```\n\n**Key insight:** The mailbox/task system is entirely file-based and independent of the terminal backend. Replacing the backend does NOT affect communication.\n\n---\n\n## Backend Detection Logic\n\n```\nFunction: aTT() — detectAndGetBackend()\n\nPriority 1: $TMUX env var present?\n  → YES: TmuxBackend (isNative=true)\n\nPriority 2: TERM_PROGRAM === \"iTerm.app\" OR $ITERM_SESSION_ID present?\n  → YES: User prefers tmux over iTerm2? (config check)\n    → YES: skip to Priority 3\n    → NO: `it2 --version` succeeds?\n      → YES: ITermBackend (isNative=true)\n      → NO: fall through\n\nPriority 3: `tmux -V` succeeds?\n  → YES: TmuxBackend (isNative=false)\n  → NO: throw Error(\"install tmux or it2\")\n\nIn-process check (separate function Bu()):\n  - Non-interactive mode → always in-process\n  - teammateMode === \"in-process\" → in-process\n  - teammateMode === \"tmux\" → never in-process\n  - teammateMode === \"auto\" → in-process if NOT inside tmux\n```\n\n**Detection functions:**\n- `Sk()` — checks `process.env.TMUX` (variable name: `TPB`)\n- `nTT()` — checks `process.env.TERM_PROGRAM === \"iTerm.app\"` OR `process.env.ITERM_SESSION_ID` exists\n\n---\n\n## Backend Interface\n\nImplicit interface (duck-typed, no explicit TypeScript interface):\n\n```typescript\ninterface PaneBackend {\n  type: string;                    // \"tmux\" | \"iterm2\"\n  displayName: string;             // \"tmux\" | \"iTerm2\"\n  supportsHideShow: boolean;       // tmux=true, iterm2=false\n\n  isAvailable(): Promise<boolean>;\n  isRunningInside(): Promise<boolean>;\n  createTeammatePaneInSwarmView(name: string, color: string): Promise<{\n    paneId: string;\n    isFirstTeammate: boolean;\n  }>;\n  sendCommandToPane(paneId: string, command: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<void>;\n  setPaneBorderColor(paneId: string, color: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<void>;\n  setPaneTitle(paneId: string, title: string, color: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<void>;\n  enablePaneBorderStatus(windowTarget?: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<void>;\n  rebalancePanes(windowTarget: string, withLeader: boolean): Promise<void>;\n  killPane(paneId: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<boolean>;\n  hidePane(paneId: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<boolean>;\n  showPane(paneId: string, targetWindow: string, isExternal?: boolean): Promise<boolean>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## tmux Backend\n\n### Commands Used\n\n| Operation | Command |\n|---|---|\n| Version check | `tmux -V` |\n| First split (with leader) | `tmux split-window -t <leaderPane> -h -l 70% -P -F \"#{pane_id}\"` |\n| Subsequent splits | `tmux split-window -t <midPane> [-v\\|-h] -P -F \"#{pane_id}\"` |\n| External session create | `tmux -L <socket> new-session -d -s claude-swarm -n swarm-view -P -F \"#{pane_id}\"` |\n| Send command | `tmux send-keys -t <paneId> <command> Enter` |\n| Border color | `tmux select-pane -t <pane> -P \"bg=default,fg=<color>\"` |\n| Border style | `tmux set-option -p -t <pane> pane-border-style \"fg=<color>\"` |\n| Active border | `tmux set-option -p -t <pane> pane-active-border-style \"fg=<color>\"` |\n| Pane title | `tmux select-pane -t <pane> -T <name>` |\n| Title format | `tmux set-option -p -t <pane> pane-border-format \"#[fg=<color>,bold] #{pane_title} #[default]\"` |\n| Border status | `tmux set-option -w -t <window> pane-border-status top` |\n| Layout (leader) | `tmux select-layout -t <window> main-vertical` + `tmux resize-pane -t <leader> -x 30%` |\n| Layout (tiled) | `tmux select-layout -t <window> tiled` |\n| Kill pane | `tmux kill-pane -t <paneId>` |\n| Hide pane | `tmux break-pane -d -s <pane> -t claude-hidden:` |\n| Show pane | `tmux join-pane -h -s <pane> -t <window>` |\n| Get pane ID | `tmux display-message -p \"#{pane_id}\"` (or `$TMUX_PANE`) |\n| Get window target | `tmux display-message [-t <pane>] -p \"#{session_name}:#{window_index}\"` |\n| List panes | `tmux list-panes -t <window> -F \"#{pane_id}\"` |\n| Pane count | `tmux list-panes -t <window> \\| wc -l` |\n\n### Split Strategy\n\n- **First teammate:** Horizontal split (`-h`), 70% width for teammate, 30% for leader\n- **Subsequent teammates:** Alternate vertical/horizontal, split from the **middle** pane of existing teammates\n  ```\n  midIndex = Math.floor((existingCount - 1) / 2)\n  isOdd = existingCount % 2 === 1  → alternate -v / -h\n  ```\n- **Rebalance after each split:** `main-vertical` layout, leader pane resized to 30%\n\n### External Session (outside tmux)\n\nWhen Claude Code is NOT inside tmux but tmux is available:\n- Creates a **separate tmux session** named `claude-swarm` with window `swarm-view`\n- Uses a **dedicated socket** (`-L <socketName>`)\n- All teammate commands use `tmux -L <socketName> ...` instead of plain `tmux`\n- Layout: `tiled` (equal distribution, no leader pane)\n\n### Color Mapping\n\n```javascript\nconst tmuxColorMap = {\n  red: \"red\",\n  blue: \"blue\",\n  green: \"green\",\n  yellow: \"yellow\",\n  purple: \"magenta\",      // tmux uses magenta for purple\n  orange: \"colour208\",\n  pink: \"colour205\",\n  cyan: \"cyan\"\n};\n```\n\n### Serialization\n\nAll pane creation operations are serialized through a **mutex** (promise chain `KW8()`) to prevent race conditions when multiple teammates are spawned simultaneously.\n\n---\n\n## iTerm2 Backend\n\n### Commands Used\n\n| Operation | Command | Output |\n|---|---|---|\n| Version check | `it2 --version` | Version string, exit 0 |\n| First split | `it2 session split -v -s <leaderSessionId>` | `Created new pane: <sessionId>` |\n| Subsequent splits | `it2 session split -s <lastPaneId>` | `Created new pane: <sessionId>` |\n| Run command | `it2 session run -s <paneId> <command>` | (empty on success) |\n| Close pane | `it2 session close -s <paneId>` | (empty on success) |\n| List sessions | `it2 session list` | Session listing (used for setup check) |\n\n### Output Parsing\n\nClaude Code parses the split output with regex:\n\n```javascript\n// Function: ZW8\nfunction parsePaneId(stdout) {\n  let match = stdout.match(/Created new pane:\\s*(.+)/);\n  if (match && match[1]) return match[1].trim();\n  return \"\";\n}\n// Empty string → throws: \"Failed to parse session ID from split output: ...\"\n```\n\n### Leader Session ID Extraction\n\nFrom `$ITERM_SESSION_ID` (format: `w0t1p12:UUID`):\n\n```javascript\n// Function: IW8\nfunction getLeaderSessionId() {\n  let envVar = process.env.ITERM_SESSION_ID;\n  if (!envVar) return null;\n  let colonIndex = envVar.indexOf(\":\");\n  if (colonIndex === -1) return null;\n  return envVar.slice(colonIndex + 1);  // extracts UUID part only\n}\n```\n\n### No-Op Operations\n\niTerm2 backend does NOT implement (all are no-ops):\n- `setPaneBorderColor()` — empty function\n- `setPaneTitle()` — empty function\n- `enablePaneBorderStatus()` — empty function\n- `rebalancePanes()` — logs \"not implemented\"\n- `hidePane()` → `return false`\n- `showPane()` → `return false`\n\n### Pane Tracking\n\n```javascript\nlet createdPanes = [];       // JPR — array of pane IDs in creation order\nlet firstPaneUsed = false;   // KPB — flag for first teammate\n\n// First split: uses leader session ID from ITERM_SESSION_ID\n// Subsequent: splits from last element in createdPanes array\n```\n\n### Serialization\n\nSame pattern as tmux — mutex via promise chain (`NW8()`) for sequential pane creation.\n\n---\n\n## In-Process Backend\n\nNo terminal multiplexer involved. Teammates run as subagents in the same Node.js process.\n\n```\n- spawn(): Creates teammate context, starts runner loop\n- Runner loop: process prompt → idle → poll mailbox → process next message\n- Auto-compaction when token limit reached\n- Shift+Down to cycle between teammates in the terminal buffer\n```\n\n---\n\n## PaneBackendExecutor\n\nWraps either TmuxBackend or ITermBackend:\n\n```typescript\nclass PaneBackendExecutor {\n  type: string;\n  backend: PaneBackend;\n  spawnedTeammates: Map<string, {paneId: string, insideTmux: boolean}>;\n\n  spawn(config): Promise<void> {\n    // 1. Generate agentId: \"sanitizedName@teamName\"\n    // 2. Assign color round-robin from: red,blue,green,yellow,purple,orange,pink,cyan\n    // 3. backend.createTeammatePaneInSwarmView(name, color)\n    // 4. If first teammate + inside tmux: enablePaneBorderStatus\n    // 5. Build full CLI command (see below)\n    // 6. backend.sendCommandToPane(paneId, command)\n    // 7. Register exit cleanup if not done\n    // 8. Send initial prompt via mailbox: n8(name, message, teamName)\n  }\n\n  sendMessage(agentId, message): Promise<void>\n  terminate(agentId, reason): Promise<void>  // graceful shutdown via mailbox\n  kill(agentId): Promise<void>               // force kill pane\n  isActive(agentId): Promise<boolean>\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Teammate Spawn Flow\n\n### CLI Command Built for Teammate\n\n```bash\ncd <cwd> && env CLAUDECODE=1 CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1 \\\n  <execPath> \\\n  --agent-id <agentId> \\\n  --agent-name <name> \\\n  --team-name <teamName> \\\n  --agent-color <color> \\\n  --parent-session-id <sessionId> \\\n  [--plan-mode-required] \\\n  [--dangerously-skip-permissions | --permission-mode acceptEdits] \\\n  [--model <model>] \\\n  [--settings <path>] \\\n  [--plugin-dir <dir>] \\\n  --teammate-mode <mode> \\\n  [--chrome | --no-chrome]\n```\n\n### Decision Tree\n\n```\nhandleSpawn(config, context):\n  if isInProcessEnabled() → handleSpawnInProcess()\n  elif config.use_splitpane !== false → handleSpawnSplitPane()  // pane in current window\n  else → handleSpawnTmuxWindow()                                 // separate tmux window\n```\n\n### Agent ID Format\n\n```javascript\nagentId = `${sanitizedName}@${teamName}`\n// @ in name replaced with -\n// Name uniqueness: append -2, -3, etc. if duplicate\n```\n\n---\n\n## Mailbox System\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/teams/{teamName}/\n├── config.json                           — team configuration\n└── messages/\n    ├── {lead-session-id}/\n    │   ├── from-teammate-1.json\n    │   └── from-teammate-2.json\n    ├── {teammate-1-session-id}/\n    │   └── from-lead.json\n    └── {teammate-2-session-id}/\n        └── from-lead.json\n```\n\n### Message Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"Your task description here\",\n  \"from\": \"team-lead\",\n  \"color\": \"blue\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-03T10:00:00.000Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### Special Messages\n\n- **Shutdown request:**\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"shutdown_request\",\n    \"requestId\": \"shutdown-<agentId>-<timestamp>\",\n    \"from\": \"team-lead\",\n    \"reason\": \"Task complete\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n### Polling\n\nTeammates poll their mailbox directory periodically via `JW8()`. Messages are read, processed, then deleted.\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n### Set by Lead When Spawning Teammate\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `CLAUDECODE` | `1` | Identifies as Claude Code process |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS` | `1` | Enables agent teams feature |\n\n### CLI Flags (not env vars)\n\n| Flag | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `--agent-id` | Unique ID: `name@teamName` |\n| `--agent-name` | Display name |\n| `--team-name` | Team identifier |\n| `--agent-color` | Color assignment |\n| `--parent-session-id` | Lead's session ID for mailbox routing |\n| `--teammate-mode` | `tmux` / `in-process` / `auto` |\n| `--plan-mode-required` | Force plan mode |\n| `--permission-mode` | `acceptEdits` or similar |\n| `--model` | LLM model to use |\n\n### Detection: \"Am I a teammate?\"\n\n```javascript\nif (process.env.CLAUDE_CODE_AGENT_ID && process.env.CLAUDE_CODE_TEAM_NAME) {\n  // I'm a teammate — enter team mode\n}\n```\n\nWait — these are passed as CLI flags (`--agent-id`, `--team-name`), not env vars. The detection likely uses the parsed CLI args, not env vars directly. The env block in the spawn command only sets `CLAUDECODE=1` and `CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1`.\n\n---\n\n## Known Bugs\n\n| Issue | Description | Relevance |\n|---|---|---|\n| [#23513](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/23513) | `send-keys` race condition: command sent before shell initialization completes | tmux only — TUIC immune |\n| [#23527](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/23527) | `pane-base-index` mismatch: CC assumes index 0 | tmux only — TUIC immune |\n| [#23615](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/23615) | Split pane breaks user's tmux layout | tmux only — TUIC immune |\n| [#24108](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24108) | Teammate stuck polling mailbox, never becomes idle | All backends |\n| [#24122](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24122) | Zellij support request (not implemented) | Shows demand for custom backends |\n| [#24384](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24384) | Windows Terminal backend request | Shows demand for custom backends |\n| [#24189](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24189) | Ghostty backend request | Shows demand for custom backends |\n| [#24292](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24292) | iTerm2 split panes not created | it2 CLI issues |\n| [#24385](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24385) | iTerm2 panes not closed on shutdown | Cleanup issue |\n| [#24771](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/24771) | Teammate disconnect from messaging | Mailbox polling |\n| [#29478](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/29478) | Korean IME corruption with `send-keys` | tmux only — TUIC immune |\n\n---\n\n## TUIC Integration Strategy\n\n### Approach: Emulate iTerm2 Backend via `it2` Shell Script\n\nThe iTerm2 backend is the simplest (5 commands, all cosmetic ops are no-ops). We emulate it by:\n\n1. **Setting PTY env vars** in `build_shell_command()`:\n   - `ITERM_SESSION_ID=w0t0p0:<pty-session-id>` — triggers iTerm2 detection\n   - `TERM_PROGRAM=iTerm.app` — satisfies TERM_PROGRAM check\n   - Prepend `~/.tuicommander/bin` to `PATH` — so our `it2` script is found\n\n2. **Providing `~/.tuicommander/bin/it2`** shell script that:\n   - `it2 --version` → prints version, exits 0\n   - `it2 session split [-v] [-s <id>]` → calls TUIC HTTP API to create session, prints `Created new pane: <session_id>`\n   - `it2 session run -s <id> <command>` → calls TUIC HTTP API to write to session\n   - `it2 session close -s <id>` → calls TUIC HTTP API to close session\n   - `it2 session list` → calls TUIC HTTP API to list sessions\n\n3. **The `it2` script communicates with TUIC via:**\n   - HTTP: `curl http://localhost:9876/sessions` (REST API already exists)\n   - Or Unix socket: direct to `~/.tuicommander/mcp.sock`\n\n### Why iTerm2 Backend (not tmux)\n\n- **5 commands** vs 15+ for tmux\n- **All visual ops are no-ops** — TUIC handles its own tab styling\n- **No layout management needed** — TUIC handles tab layout natively\n- **No `send-keys` race condition** — TUIC creates PTY first, then runs command\n- **No `pane-base-index` issues** — TUIC uses session UUIDs\n- **Simpler parsing** — just `Created new pane: <id>`\n\n### What This Gives Us\n\n- Claude Code Agent Teams works inside TUIC tabs instead of tmux panes\n- Each teammate gets its own TUIC tab with full agent detection, output parsing, sidebar icon\n- The mailbox/task system works unchanged (file-based, backend-independent)\n- TUIC can show team status in sidebar, aggregate notifications, etc.\n\n### Risks\n\n1. **CC updates may change it2 interface** — monitor decompiled binary after updates\n2. **TERM_PROGRAM change from ghostty to iTerm.app** — may affect other terminal detection\n3. **it2 version expectations** — CC may start checking version compatibility\n4. **execSync vs shell** — need to verify that `it2` shell script is found by Node.js `execSync`\n\n### Future: Proposing a TUIC Backend to Anthropic\n\nOnce the it2 emulation works, we can propose adding TUICommander as a native backend. Evidence: GitHub issues #24122 (Zellij), #24384 (Windows Terminal), #24189 (Ghostty) show demand for custom backends.\n\n---\n\n## Verification Checklist\n\nAfter Claude Code updates, verify these haven't changed:\n\n- [ ] `it2 session split` output format: `Created new pane: <id>`\n- [ ] `IW8()` extracts UUID from `ITERM_SESSION_ID` after `:`\n- [ ] `nTT()` checks `TERM_PROGRAM === \"iTerm.app\"` or `ITERM_SESSION_ID`\n- [ ] Backend detection priority: TMUX → iTerm2 → tmux external → error\n- [ ] CLI flags for teammate spawn (--agent-id, --team-name, etc.)\n- [ ] Mailbox directory structure: `~/.claude/teams/{name}/messages/`\n\n### How to Re-Verify\n\nThe binary is installed at `~/.claude/local/bin/claude`. It's a Bun compiled JS bundle. To extract and search:\n\n```bash\n# Find the binary\nls -la ~/.claude/local/bin/claude\n\n# Search for key strings in the binary\nstrings ~/.claude/local/bin/claude | grep -i \"Created new pane\"\nstrings ~/.claude/local/bin/claude | grep -i \"session split\"\nstrings ~/.claude/local/bin/claude | grep -i \"ITERM_SESSION_ID\"\nstrings ~/.claude/local/bin/claude | grep -i \"pane-border-status\"\nstrings ~/.claude/local/bin/claude | grep -i \"teammate-mode\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## it2 CLI Reference (mkusaka/it2 — Python)\n\nThe `it2` tool used by Claude Code is [mkusaka/it2](https://github.com/mkusaka/it2) (Python, pip install).\n\n**NOT** [tmc/it2](https://github.com/tmc/it2) (Go) which has different output format (`Session split successfully. New session ID: ...`).\n\n### Installation\n\n```bash\npip install it2\n```\n\n### Key Source Files\n\n- `src/it2/commands/session.py` — implements split, run, close, list\n- Output on split: `click.echo(f\"Created new pane: {new_session.session_id}\")`\n",
