            "content": "# Agent Teams Bridge — TUIC as Claude Code Teammate Backend\n\n**Status:** `validated`\n**Created:** 2026-03-03\n**Priority:** P1\n\n## Problem\n\nClaude Code Agent Teams spawns teammates in tmux panes or iTerm2 splits. When running inside TUICommander, teammates should open as TUIC tabs instead — giving users full agent detection, output parsing, sidebar integration, and terminal management.\n\n## Solution\n\nEmulate the iTerm2 `it2` CLI interface so Claude Code uses TUIC tabs as its teammate backend. The iTerm2 backend is the simplest (5 commands, all visual ops are no-ops) and maps cleanly to TUIC's existing HTTP API.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Phase 1: PTY Environment (Rust)\n\nModify `build_shell_command()` in `pty.rs` to:\n- Set `ITERM_SESSION_ID=w0t0p0:<session_id>` — triggers iTerm2 detection\n- Change `TERM_PROGRAM` from `ghostty` to `iTerm.app`  — satisfies check\n- Prepend `~/.tuicommander/bin` to `PATH`\n\n**Risk:** Changing `TERM_PROGRAM` may affect other terminal detection. Need conditional logic — only set when agent teams feature is enabled.\n\n### Phase 2: `it2` Shell Script\n\nCreate `~/.tuicommander/bin/it2` — a ~30 line shell script:\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# TUIC it2 compatibility shim\nTUIC_PORT=\"${TUIC_HTTP_PORT:-9876}\"\ncase \"$1 $2\" in\n  \"--version\")     echo \"1.0.0\"; exit 0 ;;\n  \"session split\") # parse -v, -s flags → POST /sessions → print \"Created new pane: <id>\" ;;\n  \"session run\")   # parse -s flag + command → POST /sessions/{id}/write ;;\n  \"session close\") # parse -s flag → DELETE /sessions/{id} ;;\n  \"session list\")  # GET /sessions → format output ;;\nesac\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Integration\n\nWhen a session is created via the it2 shim:\n- Sidebar auto-creates tab (already works for HTTP-created sessions)\n- Agent detection kicks in when Claude Code starts in the new tab\n- Team status visible in sidebar icons\n\n### Phase 4: Rename Binary\n\nRename `tuic-mcp-bridge` → `tuic-bridge` (drop \"mcp\" from name since it now serves multiple protocols).\n\n## Research\n\nFull technical documentation: `docs/research/claude-code-agent-teams.md`\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Should the it2 emulation be opt-in (config toggle) or always-on?\n- How to handle `TERM_PROGRAM` change — ghostty was chosen for Claude Code compat, but iTerm.app is needed for agent teams detection\n- Should we propose this to Anthropic as a new native backend?\n",
