            "content": "# Agent Teams Integration (it2 Shim)\n\n**Status:** `designed`\n**Source:** Claude Code Agent Teams feature (experimental, Feb 2026)\n**Updated:** 2026-03-03 — switched from tmux shim to it2 (iTerm2 CLI) shim\n**Research:** [`docs/research/claude-code-agent-teams.md`](../docs/research/claude-code-agent-teams.md)\n\n## What\n\nTUICommander replaces tmux/iTerm2 as the display layer for Claude Code Agent Teams. When a lead Claude Code instance spawns teammates, a scoped `it2` shim intercepts the call and creates TUIC tabs instead.\n\n## Why it2 Instead of tmux\n\nThe previous design shimmed `tmux` (15+ commands, complex layout management, `send-keys` race conditions). The **iTerm2 backend is far simpler:**\n\n| | tmux backend | iTerm2 backend |\n|---|---|---|\n| Commands to implement | 15+ | **5** |\n| Visual ops (borders, titles) | Must implement | **All no-ops** |\n| Layout management | Must implement | **No-op** |\n| Race conditions | `send-keys` before shell init | **None** (direct `session run`) |\n| Pane ID format | `%0`, `%1` (tmux-specific) | **Any string** (UUID works) |\n| Dependencies | `socat` or `/dev/tcp` for IPC | **Just `curl`** |\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nClaude Code (lead in TUI tab)\n  → detects ITERM_SESSION_ID in env → selects iTerm2 backend\n  → calls `it2 session split -v -s <leader-id>`\n  → calls `it2 session run -s <pane-id> <command>`\n\n~/.tuicommander/bin/it2  (shell script shim, ~30 lines)\n  |-- --version                        → echo \"1.0.0\"\n  |-- session split [-v] [-s <id>]     → curl POST /sessions → print \"Created new pane: <id>\"\n  |-- session run -s <id> <command>    → curl POST /sessions/<id>/write\n  |-- session close -s <id>            → curl DELETE /sessions/<id>\n  \\-- session list                     → curl GET /sessions\n```\n\n### Communication (unchanged, file-based)\n\nThe mailbox and task list are completely independent of the terminal backend:\n```\n~/.claude/teams/{teamName}/messages/  — teammate ↔ lead messages\n~/.claude/tasks/{teamName}/           — shared task list with file locking\n```\n\n## PTY Environment Changes\n\nIn `build_shell_command()` (pty.rs), when agent teams shim is enabled:\n\n```rust\n// Trigger iTerm2 detection in Claude Code\ncmd.env(\"ITERM_SESSION_ID\", format!(\"w0t0p0:{}\", session_id));\ncmd.env(\"TERM_PROGRAM\", \"iTerm.app\");\n\n// Ensure our it2 shim is found first\nlet tuic_bin = config_dir().join(\"bin\");\nlet path = format!(\"{}:{}\", tuic_bin.display(), std::env::var(\"PATH\").unwrap_or_default());\ncmd.env(\"PATH\", path);\n\n// Also pass HTTP port so the shim knows where to call\ncmd.env(\"TUIC_HTTP_PORT\", http_port.to_string());\n```\n\n**TERM_PROGRAM concern:** Changing from `ghostty` to `iTerm.app` may affect Claude Code's terminal capability detection. The change MUST be conditional — only when agent teams shim is enabled in settings.\n\n## The `it2` Shim Script\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# TUICommander it2 compatibility shim for Claude Code Agent Teams\n# Emulates mkusaka/it2 (Python) CLI interface\nset -euo pipefail\n\nTUIC_PORT=\"${TUIC_HTTP_PORT:-9876}\"\nTUIC_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:${TUIC_PORT}\"\n\ncase \"${1:-}\" in\n  --version)\n    echo \"1.0.0\"\n    exit 0\n    ;;\n  session)\n    shift\n    case \"${1:-}\" in\n      split)\n        shift\n        # Parse flags: -v (vertical, ignored), -s <session_id>\n        while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n          case \"$1\" in\n            -v) shift ;;\n            -s) shift; PARENT_ID=\"$1\"; shift ;;\n            *) shift ;;\n          esac\n        done\n        # Create new session via TUIC HTTP API\n        RESP=$(curl -sf \"${TUIC_URL}/sessions\" \\\n          -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n          -d '{\"rows\": 24, \"cols\": 80}')\n        SESSION_ID=$(echo \"$RESP\" | grep -o '\"session_id\":\"[^\"]*\"' | cut -d'\"' -f4)\n        echo \"Created new pane: ${SESSION_ID}\"\n        ;;\n      run)\n        shift\n        # Parse: -s <session_id> <command...>\n        SESSION_ID=\"\"\n        while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n          case \"$1\" in\n            -s) shift; SESSION_ID=\"$1\"; shift ;;\n            *) break ;;\n          esac\n        done\n        COMMAND=\"$*\"\n        curl -sf \"${TUIC_URL}/sessions/${SESSION_ID}/write\" \\\n          -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n          -d \"{\\\"data\\\": \\\"${COMMAND}\\n\\\"}\" > /dev/null\n        ;;\n      close)\n        shift\n        SESSION_ID=\"\"\n        while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n          case \"$1\" in\n            -s) shift; SESSION_ID=\"$1\"; shift ;;\n            *) shift ;;\n          esac\n        done\n        curl -sf -X DELETE \"${TUIC_URL}/sessions/${SESSION_ID}\" > /dev/null\n        ;;\n      list)\n        curl -sf \"${TUIC_URL}/sessions\"\n        ;;\n      *)\n        echo \"Unknown session subcommand: ${1:-}\" >&2\n        exit 1\n        ;;\n    esac\n    ;;\n  *)\n    echo \"Unknown command: ${1:-}\" >&2\n    exit 1\n    ;;\nesac\n```\n\n## Components Needed\n\n| Component | Location | Purpose |\n|-----------|----------|---------|\n| it2 shim script | `~/.tuicommander/bin/it2` | Intercepts it2 commands, calls TUIC HTTP |\n| PTY env injection | `src-tauri/src/pty.rs` | Sets ITERM_SESSION_ID, TERM_PROGRAM, PATH |\n| Settings config | Settings store | Persists agent-teams toggle |\n| Settings UI | SettingsPanel | Toggle switch |\n| Auto-install | `src-tauri/src/agent_mcp.rs` | Creates bin dir + writes it2 script |\n| Integration tests | `tests/it2-shim/` | Verify shim handles known CC it2 commands |\n\n## Configurable via Settings\n\n- **Enable Agent Teams shim** (toggle, off by default) — Controls env injection + shim installation\n- **Team tab grouping** (toggle) — Visual distinction for teammate tabs (e.g., colored border)\n- **Auto-focus new teammates** (toggle) — Switch to new tab when teammate spawns\n\n## Bridge Rename\n\nAs part of this work, rename `tuic-mcp-bridge` → `tuic-bridge` since it now serves multiple protocols (MCP stdio + it2 compat potential).\n\n## Risks\n\n1. **CC's it2 interface is internal** — can change without notice. Mitigation: verification script + integration tests\n2. **Agent Teams feature may be redesigned** — it's still experimental. Monitor CC releases.\n3. **TERM_PROGRAM change** — must be conditional, not global\n4. **curl dependency** — available on all platforms, minimal risk\n\n## NOT in Scope (YAGNI)\n\n- Task list UI visualization (CC manages via `~/.claude/tasks/`)\n- Inter-teammate message UI (filesystem-based, works without us)\n- Custom team creation UI (user types naturally in Claude Code)\n- tmux backend shim (abandoned in favor of simpler it2 approach)\n- Contributing upstream to CC (separate effort, after we demonstrate it works)\n",
